{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have opportunity ready. Need to decide vote based on record. The prompt includes extensive arguments from both sides. Must use admitted evidence only. The record shows many reports that publicly released the note before May 8, described as purported suicide note, with caveats. The market rule requires credible reporting that note was written by Epstein and intended as suicide note or final message. The evidence: multiple reputable outlets (Reuters, NPR, BBC, Guardian, AP/PBS, Courthouse News, FOX) reported it as \"purported\" or \"alleged\". They use \"purported\" but that still counts as credible reporting? They also note lack of authentication, DOJ first seeing, and uncertainties. Handwriting experts say common authorship but not definitive.\n\nWe must decide if preponderance met. Considering credible reporting, there is a consensus among sources that it was a purported suicide note. The caveats suggest uncertainty, but credible reporting includes caveated language; does that satisfy \"credibly reported to have been written by Epstein\"? Probably yes, as the market rule says \"credibly reported\" not \"authenticated\". The reports are credible (Reuters, NPR, BBC, Guardian). They all use \"purported\" and note lack of authentication, but they still report that it was written by Epstein. That seems to meet the requirement. Intent: the note contains language about \"time to say goodbye\" and is described as suicide note by outlets. So likely meets.\n\nThus I as council member should vote demonstrated. Provide concise rationale max three sentences.\n\nProceed to submit vote.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a007bc3548279719","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782792922714,"responseId":"gen-1782792922-ixpjz21dJrBHy5gZCk2Y"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have opportunity ready. Need to decide vote based on record. The prompt includes extensive arguments from both sides. Must use admitted evidence only. The record shows many reports that publicly released the note before May 8, described as purported suicide note, with caveats. The market rule requires credible reporting that note was written by Epstein and intended as suicide note or final message. The evidence: multiple reputable outlets (Reuters, NPR, BBC, Guardian, AP/PBS, Courthouse News, FOX) reported it as \"purported\" or \"alleged\". They use \"purported\" but that still counts as credible reporting? They also note lack of authentication, DOJ first seeing, and uncertainties. Handwriting experts say common authorship but not definitive.\n\nWe must decide if preponderance met. Considering credible reporting, there is a consensus among sources that it was a purported suicide note. The caveats suggest uncertainty, but credible reporting includes caveated language; does that satisfy \"credibly reported to have been written by Epstein\"? Probably yes, as the market rule says \"credibly reported\" not \"authenticated\". The reports are credible (Reuters, NPR, BBC, Guardian). They all use \"purported\" and note lack of authentication, but they still report that it was written by Epstein. That seems to meet the requirement. Intent: the note contains language about \"time to say goodbye\" and is described as suicide note by outlets. So likely meets.\n\nThus I as council member should vote demonstrated. Provide concise rationale max three sentences.\n\nProceed to submit vote.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a007bc3548279719","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782792922714,"responseId":"gen-1782792922-ixpjz21dJrBHy5gZCk2Y"}}
