ludes caveated language; does that satisfy \"credibly reported to have been written by Epstein\"? Probably yes, as the market rule says \"credibly reported\" not \"authenticated\". The reports are credible (Reuters, NPR, BBC, Guardian). They all use \"purported\" and note lack of authentication, but they still report that it was written by Epstein. That seems to meet the requirement. Intent: the note contains language about \"time to say goodbye\" and is described as suicide note by outlets. So likely meets.\n\nThus I as council member should vote demonstrated. Provide concise rationale max three sentences.\n\nProceed to submit vote.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a007bc3548279719","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Multiple reputable outlets publicly reported the unsealed document before May 8 as a purported Jeffrey Epstein suicide note, and the note’s language and consensus reporting satisfy the market’s credible‑reporting standard for authorship and intent at a pre"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\":\"aar_submit_council_vote\",\"args\":\"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Multiple reputable outlets publicly reported the unsealed document before May 8 as a purported Jeffrey Epstein suicide note, and the note’s language and consensus reporting satisfy the market’s credible‑reporting standard for authorship and intent at a pre","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782792922714,"responseId":"gen-1782792922-ixpjz21dJrBHy5gZCk2Y"}}
